Actually, I'm a little scared.

1426
00:55:24,267 --> 00:55:27,533
Those gulls might peck at your hand.

1427
00:55:27,533 --> 00:55:28,333
They won't.

1428
00:55:28,733 --> 00:55:30,633
They're already used to being fed now.

1429
00:55:31,167 --> 00:55:32,167
They kind of know the routine.

1430
00:55:33,267 --> 00:55:35,567
I thought they'd already been trained.

1431
00:55:38,700 --> 00:55:40,133
Be careful in those high heels.

1432
00:55:40,500 --> 00:55:41,633
It's fine, not a big deal.

1433
00:55:42,267 --> 00:55:43,100
You go down first.

1434
00:55:43,367 --> 00:55:45,167
You should be more careful with your shoes.

1435
00:55:49,767 --> 00:55:50,533
Take it slow.

1436
00:55:50,767 --> 00:55:52,033
It's okay.

1437
00:55:54,167 --> 00:55:56,200
These steps are easier to go down than I thought.

1438
00:56:02,433 --> 00:56:03,467
They can even swim.

1439
00:56:05,367 --> 00:56:07,200
Why are they kind of cute?

1440
00:56:12,233 --> 00:56:12,600
Really.

1441
00:56:12,600 --> 00:56:14,433
The seagull doesn't have any fries left to eat.

1442
00:56:14,433 --> 00:56:16,033
I'm about to finish them.

1443
00:56:16,033 --> 00:56:16,600
It's okay.

1444
00:56:17,167 --> 00:56:18,300
It wouldn't eat them anyway.

1445
00:56:18,500 --> 00:56:19,633
You're the one eating them, right?

1446
00:56:23,667 --> 00:56:26,133
The scenery here is so nice.

1447
00:56:30,367 --> 00:56:31,733
So how do we give it to the seagull?

1448
00:56:31,733 --> 00:56:32,467
Just do it like this.

1449
00:56:34,167 --> 00:56:35,400
Can it see?

1450
00:56:36,100 --> 00:56:37,333
Put it on your hand.

1451
00:56:37,333 --> 00:56:37,700
It's fine.

1452
00:56:37,700 --> 00:56:38,367
You go first.

1453
00:56:38,367 --> 00:56:39,467
Okay, you give it to me.

1454
00:56:40,400 --> 00:56:41,300
Is it a seagull?

1455
00:56:41,300 --> 00:56:42,533
Aren't they known for having good eyesight?

1456
00:56:42,533 --> 00:56:43,200
Yes.

1457
00:56:43,567 --> 00:56:45,200
Are you sure it won't bite my hand?

1458
00:56:46,100 --> 00:56:47,767
I can show you how first.

1459
00:56:49,400 --> 00:56:50,100
Here you go.

1460
00:56:51,367 --> 00:56:52,200
You need to attract it.

1461
00:56:52,767 --> 00:56:53,633
Learn how to attract it.

1462
00:56:56,800 --> 00:56:58,200
Have you ever fed one before?

1463
00:56:58,600 --> 00:56:59,267
No.

1464
00:56:59,267 --> 00:57:00,267
No.

1465
00:57:02,100 --> 00:57:03,200
Then how can you show me?

1466
00:57:03,200 --> 00:57:04,200
So you're just like me.

1467
00:57:04,200 --> 00:57:05,800
I've seen it in videos.

1468
00:57:06,433 --> 00:57:07,767
They do it like this and the seagull comes over.

1469
00:57:08,267 --> 00:57:09,133
It feels like this way...

1470
00:57:10,500 --> 00:57:11,333
Or maybe we should get a little closer.

1471
00:57:11,333 --> 00:57:12,500
It's already full.

1472
00:57:15,667 --> 00:57:17,167
Just hold your hand up like this.

1473
00:57:17,167 --> 00:57:19,600
Or you could try tossing a little bit forward first.

1474
00:57:20,100 --> 00:57:21,600
Let them know there's food over here too.

1475
00:57:26,600 --> 00:57:27,633
Look

1476
00:57:30,367 --> 00:57:32,200
It has to be Wo, right?

1477
00:57:36,600 --> 00:57:37,467
That's good.

1478
00:57:38,167 --> 00:57:39,200
I'm going to throw a French fry.

1479
00:57:39,200 --> 00:57:40,300
Let's see if they'll eat it.

1480
00:57:40,300 --> 00:57:41,700
I don't believe they won't eat it.

1481
00:57:42,200 --> 00:57:43,300
They really aren't eating it.

1482
00:57:46,133 --> 00:57:47,500
They don't like eating the long ones.

1483
00:57:47,800 --> 00:57:49,033
You're in charge of feeding them.

1484
00:57:49,033 --> 00:57:50,800
I'll supply you with more.

1485
00:57:53,067 --> 00:57:54,733
You think it's like a dog catching a frisbee, right?

1486
00:57:56,033 --> 00:57:57,533
Look, it caught it.

1487
00:57:57,767 --> 00:57:59,267
They're getting closer and closer to us.

1488
00:58:00,133 --> 00:58:01,767
They know these two keep feeding them.

1489
00:58:01,767 --> 00:58:03,600
There's a big feeder over here.

1490
00:58:04,700 --> 00:58:05,733
Where did they go?

1491
00:58:07,433 --> 00:58:09,033
It's really beautiful.

1492
00:58:10,233 --> 00:58:11,800
So beautiful.

1493
00:58:14,400 --> 00:58:19,200
When I get off the plane, I want to record a selfie.

1494
00:58:19,400 --> 00:58:21,367
We promised we'd go to Qingdao together.

1495
00:58:21,367 --> 00:58:22,667
We had a great time.

1496
00:58:23,300 --> 00:58:25,633
Actually, it was to send Hou back to work.

1497
00:58:27,800 --> 00:58:29,267
He didn't want to go back by himself.

1498
00:58:29,267 --> 00:58:31,100
So he said he'd take me to Qingdao for fun.

1499
00:58:33,167 --> 00:58:34,500
Just teasing you.

1500
00:58:34,500 --> 00:58:35,633
No, I can't take being teased.

1501
00:58:35,633 --> 00:58:38,033
Come on, cheer me up.

1502
00:58:38,033 --> 00:58:38,700
How should I cheer you up?

1503
00:58:38,700 --> 00:58:39,733
Just give me a kiss and it'll be fine.

1504
00:58:44,500 --> 00:58:45,667
Your laugh is hilarious.

1505
00:58:47,500 --> 00:58:48,700
I love my hometown.

1506
00:58:49,100 --> 00:58:50,200
But I love even more

1507
00:58:51,467 --> 00:58:53,033
that you came to visit my hometown.

1508
00:58:53,033 --> 00:58:54,633
Let me take you to Shanghai for a trip.

1509
00:58:54,633 --> 00:58:55,233
Sure.

1510
00:58:57,100 --> 00:58:58,700
Are there any attractions?

1511
00:58:58,700 --> 00:58:59,700
Guo Guo's place.

1512
00:59:02,267 --> 00:59:03,433
That made me laugh.

1513
00:59:04,633 --> 00:59:07,000
Honestly, I think I should live here for a year.

1514
00:59:07,233 --> 00:59:08,500
You have to come over in the future.

1515
00:59:08,500 --> 00:59:09,433
Relax, relax.

1516
00:59:09,433 --> 00:59:10,400
Take a break.

1517
00:59:11,367 --> 00:59:12,200
Okay.

1518
00:59:18,667 --> 00:59:20,200
I'm planning to do something big.

1519
00:59:20,200 --> 00:59:20,400
I'm planning to do something big.

1520
00:59:20,400 --> 00:59:21,100
Because in a couple of days

1521
00:59:21,100 --> 00:59:22,067
it will be the

1522
00:59:22,067 --> 00:59:23,033
one-month anniversary for me and Kaka.

1523
00:59:23,033 --> 00:59:25,133
I'm planning to secretly go to Shanghai to see her.

1524
00:59:25,133 --> 00:59:26,333
To give her a surprise.

1525
00:59:28,433 --> 00:59:30,033
Heading out now.

1526
00:59:30,667 --> 00:59:32,067
It's still dark outside.

1527
00:59:59,700 --> 01:00:00,667
My hands are freezing.

1528
01:00:28,500 --> 01:00:30,333
Okay, three, two, one, go.

1529
01:00:30,333 --> 01:00:31,067
Turn around.

1530
01:00:31,600 --> 01:00:33,367
Okay, lift it up for a photo.

1531
01:00:33,367 --> 01:00:34,633
Alright, look happier.

1532
01:00:37,000 --> 01:00:38,467
Okay, let's replay and check it.

1533
01:00:42,200 --> 01:00:43,633
Let's come over and take a look at this.

1534
01:01:05,633 --> 01:01:06,200
This one.

1535
01:01:07,167 --> 01:01:10,100
This is our cameraman for the show.

1536
01:01:11,233 --> 01:01:12,000
That one too.

1537
01:01:21,167 --> 01:01:22,100
So familiar.

1538
01:01:22,100 --> 01:01:23,233
Long time no see.

1539
01:01:23,233 --> 01:01:24,367
He looks so calm.

1540
01:01:24,367 --> 01:01:26,167
He thinks I can't recognize him just because he's wearing a mask.

1541
01:01:26,167 --> 01:01:28,300
Is today some kind of behind-the-scenes special?

1542
01:01:30,800 --> 01:01:32,733
Will my Lao Wan show up later?

1543
01:01:35,067 --> 01:01:36,233
So what if you have a man?

1544
01:01:38,400 --> 01:01:40,533
Teacher Zheng, your bangs are about to get crooked from laughing.

1545
01:01:51,467 --> 01:01:53,167
Weren't you sick?

1546
01:01:53,167 --> 01:01:54,533
I was fooling you.

1547
01:01:55,167 --> 01:01:56,767
Of course I was fooling you.

1548
01:01:58,367 --> 01:02:00,067
That's so nice.

1549
01:02:00,200 --> 01:02:01,633
Isn't this a surprise?

1550
01:02:02,800 --> 01:02:03,400
Alright.

1551
01:02:03,400 --> 01:02:04,533
Everyone, let's break up.

1552
01:02:04,800 --> 01:02:05,633
Let's go.

1553
01:02:05,633 --> 01:02:07,200
Isn't this our one-month anniversary?

1554
01:02:07,500 --> 01:02:09,467
Didn't I promise you I'd do this?

1555
01:02:11,533 --> 01:02:12,200
Right?

1556
01:02:12,700 --> 01:02:14,533
I told you I'd come see you in secret.

1557
01:02:16,800 --> 01:02:17,567
Lao Wan.

1558
01:02:20,067 --> 01:02:20,600
I want a kiss.

1559
01:02:29,367 --> 01:02:31,367
Take a look at the gift I prepared for you first.

1560
01:02:32,333 --> 01:02:33,100
Cake.

1561
01:02:33,100 --> 01:02:34,567
It's my favorite.

1562
01:02:34,567 --> 01:02:36,100
Let me unwrap the cake for you first.

1563
01:02:36,400 --> 01:02:38,533
I'll do it, let me do it myself.

1564
01:02:39,800 --> 01:02:41,533
Let me take a look.

1565
01:02:42,333 --> 01:02:44,333
If that doesn't work, you can cut it open.

1566
01:02:44,333 --> 01:02:45,067
I don't want to.

1567
01:02:45,767 --> 01:02:46,267
Puppy.

1568
01:02:47,000 --> 01:02:48,233
Thirty days.

1569
01:02:49,800 --> 01:02:51,100
This side is your cup.

1570
01:02:51,367 --> 01:02:52,333
This side is my cup.

1571
01:02:56,267 --> 01:02:57,667
Did you make this one yourself too?

1572
01:02:57,800 --> 01:02:58,400
Yeah.

1573
01:02:59,067 --> 01:03:00,000
Lao Wan.

1574
01:03:01,367 --> 01:03:01,733
This.

1575
01:03:01,733 --> 01:03:02,567
Come here.

1576
01:03:06,533 --> 01:03:07,300
What?

1577
01:03:07,300 --> 01:03:07,800
Kiss.

1578
01:03:14,467 --> 01:03:15,433
What is this thing?

1579
01:03:15,433 --> 01:03:17,000
You can unwrap this one yourself too.

1580
01:03:19,800 --> 01:03:21,400
This is so thoughtful.

1581
01:03:21,400 --> 01:03:23,500
I worked on this until 2 a.m. on Monday.

1582
01:03:24,433 --> 01:03:25,700
Is this one of those custom-made ones?

1583
01:03:25,700 --> 01:03:27,533
Yes, this is a photo Lao Xia took of us.

1584
01:03:27,533 --> 01:03:28,133
Be careful.

1585
01:03:28,133 --> 01:03:28,800
It might fall apart.

1586
01:03:30,067 --> 01:03:30,633
Alright, let's eat cake.

1587
01:03:30,633 --> 01:03:31,700
Okay, let's eat cake.

1588
01:03:31,700 --> 01:03:33,200
Eat cake.

1589
01:03:35,467 --> 01:03:36,767
We're eating it in such a unique way.

1590
01:03:41,100 --> 01:03:42,067
It smells so good.

1591
01:03:47,600 --> 01:03:48,233
Delicious.

1592
01:03:54,033 --> 01:03:55,000
There's Oreo inside.

1593
01:04:00,600 --> 01:04:01,500
This is amazing.

1594
01:04:03,633 --> 01:04:04,333
Bet you didn't expect that.

1595
01:04:05,200 --> 01:04:05,800
I really didn't.

1596
01:04:06,267 --> 01:04:07,733
Isn't this our first anniversary?

1597
01:04:09,233 --> 01:04:11,667
I thought we definitely had to celebrate it.

1598
01:04:12,200 --> 01:04:15,133
Let's go take one of those close-up photos.

1599
01:04:15,333 --> 01:04:16,233
Is it the kind I mentioned?

1600
01:04:16,233 --> 01:04:17,800
The kind of close-up photo you take in the elevator.

1601
01:04:18,767 --> 01:04:20,333
And after we finish taking the photos,

1602
01:04:20,333 --> 01:04:21,700
we can just make plans as we like.

1603
01:04:21,700 --> 01:04:23,367
We could ask Xia Xia to have a meal together,

1604
01:04:23,367 --> 01:04:23,700
or

1605
01:04:23,700 --> 01:04:24,267
we could just eat together ourselves.

1606
01:04:24,267 --> 01:04:24,600
As agreed,

1607
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:26,267
Wo Wo has already picked a place for tonight.

1608
01:04:26,267 --> 01:04:27,433
I just told Wo Wo as well.

1609
01:04:27,433 --> 01:04:29,233
I said we should invite Xiao Hou tonight too.

1610
01:04:29,333 --> 01:04:30,000
Xiao Hou will be there too.

1611
01:04:30,700 --> 01:04:32,700
Then Xia Xia said,

1612
01:04:32,700 --> 01:04:33,433
she said,

1613
01:04:34,400 --> 01:04:35,533
"I'm not going, right?"

1614
01:04:35,533 --> 01:04:38,167
She said, "Have you considered how I feel?"

1615
01:04:39,200 --> 01:04:39,533
Isn't that nice?

1616
01:04:39,533 --> 01:04:40,633
The four of us keeping her company.

1617
01:04:40,633 --> 01:04:41,167
Isn't that great?

1618
01:04:41,600 --> 01:04:42,600
And actually, tonight,

1619
01:04:42,600 --> 01:04:43,800
Xia Xia was supposed to stay at my place.

1620
01:04:44,400 --> 01:04:45,500
But now it's just very...

1621
01:04:45,700 --> 01:04:46,700
She can still stay at your place.

1622
01:04:53,700 --> 01:04:54,467
Old Xia,

1623
01:04:55,033 --> 01:04:55,633
I'll leave this here for you.

1624
01:04:55,633 --> 01:04:56,567
Thank you.

1625
01:04:56,567 --> 01:04:57,167
No problem.

1626
01:04:57,167 --> 01:04:57,567
See you in a bit.

1627
01:04:57,567 --> 01:04:58,133
Goodbye.

1628
01:04:58,133 --> 01:04:59,200
See you later, see you tonight.

1629
01:05:14,533 --> 01:05:16,033
It has always been with me.

1630
01:05:17,200 --> 01:05:19,133
It's fine. After everything that happened today,

1631
01:05:19,133 --> 01:05:20,633
I feel like this won't

1632
01:05:20,633 --> 01:05:22,400
affect me much anymore.

1633
01:05:25,367 --> 01:05:26,633
The last time we met,

1634
01:05:28,233 --> 01:05:30,400
No.

1635
01:05:34,333 --> 01:05:36,500
I want to treasure it.

1636
01:05:40,267 --> 01:05:43,233
You acted out the illness part so well.

1637
01:05:45,233 --> 01:05:46,567
The buildup was really good.

1638
01:05:46,567 --> 01:05:48,100
It didn't feel abrupt.

1639
01:05:48,533 --> 01:05:49,467
I'm really happy.

1640
01:05:58,400 --> 01:05:59,000
Hello.

1641
01:05:59,000 --> 01:05:59,667
Hello.

1642
01:06:00,500 --> 01:06:02,467
We want to take some photos of the elevator.

1643
01:06:02,467 --> 01:06:03,000
Okay.

1644
01:06:03,000 --> 01:06:04,733
Do you have a favorite elevator?

1645
01:06:05,033 --> 01:06:05,633
We've already looked.

1646
01:06:05,633 --> 01:06:07,267
We just want to take photos of the classic one.

1647
01:06:10,400 --> 01:06:11,500
Does this one look good?

1648
01:06:12,400 --> 01:06:13,267
I think it's pretty good.

1649
01:06:13,467 --> 01:06:14,400
The lighting is decent.

1650
01:06:14,400 --> 01:06:15,233
You press it.

1651
01:06:15,633 --> 01:06:16,200
I'll press it.

1652
01:06:17,100 --> 01:06:18,100
Press the middle, right?

1653
01:06:23,633 --> 01:06:24,767
Make a heart gesture.

1654
01:06:35,100 --> 01:06:36,033
Like a big monkey.

1655
01:07:03,367 --> 01:07:03,733
Kidnapping.

1656
01:07:04,667 --> 01:07:06,067
"Kidnap" this woman.

1657
01:07:06,267 --> 01:07:07,000
That's great.

1658
01:07:15,167 --> 01:07:16,533
You look so small.

1659
01:07:16,533 --> 01:07:18,067
My face is already small.

1660
01:07:21,033 --> 01:07:21,733
Compared like this,

1661
01:07:21,733 --> 01:07:23,433
why does my face look so big?

1662
01:07:23,600 --> 01:07:24,267
Kiss.

1663
01:07:33,633 --> 01:07:34,600
What's going on?

1664
01:07:34,600 --> 01:07:35,233
Why?

1665
01:07:36,167 --> 01:07:37,767
Is this gesture not allowed?

1666
01:07:38,733 --> 01:07:39,367
No way.

1667
01:07:42,667 --> 01:07:43,267
What's happening?

1668
01:07:43,267 --> 01:07:43,633
Let's do it again.

1669
01:07:48,633 --> 01:07:49,467
What kind of loophole is this?

1670
01:07:49,467 --> 01:07:50,200
I really didn't know it would

1671
01:07:50,200 --> 01:07:50,567
Give it to me.

1672
01:07:50,567 --> 01:07:51,233
You try it.

1673
01:07:51,233 --> 01:07:52,567
Let me try. Is it this one?

1674
01:07:57,733 --> 01:07:59,267
I suspect you want to steal a kiss from me.

1675
01:08:01,367 --> 01:08:02,033
You guessed right.

1676
01:08:03,733 --> 01:08:04,633
No, don't move.

1677
01:08:12,000 --> 01:08:13,233
You're pinning me against the wall.

1678
01:08:15,700 --> 01:08:18,400
I can't get it in the shot.

1679
01:08:18,633 --> 01:08:19,200
Like this.

1680
01:08:20,600 --> 01:08:22,033
Use your other hand to pin me.

1681
01:08:22,367 --> 01:08:23,000
Like this.

1682
01:08:27,400 --> 01:08:29,033
Take the picture upside down.

1683
01:08:29,333 --> 01:08:30,133
Go ahead and take it.

1684
01:08:37,167 --> 01:08:38,200
Is this really a wall slam?

1685
01:08:50,033 --> 01:08:50,800
Okay.

1686
01:08:50,800 --> 01:08:52,367
Alright, give me the camera.

1687
01:08:53,067 --> 01:08:53,800
Please sit for a moment.

1688
01:08:53,800 --> 01:08:54,500
I'll help you transfer the photos.

1689
01:08:54,500 --> 01:08:55,033
Okay.

1690
01:08:55,800 --> 01:08:57,467
We only took 39 photos.

1691
01:08:57,467 --> 01:08:59,267
No, there are 116.

1692
01:09:01,700 --> 01:09:03,800
I'll send them in batches, it's a bit more stable.

1693
01:09:03,800 --> 01:09:04,733
Yes.

1694
01:09:05,000 --> 01:09:05,533
Is it done?

1695
01:09:07,567 --> 01:09:09,633
Almost, there's still one receipt.

1696
01:09:10,767 --> 01:09:12,267
The rest are in this small envelope.

1697
01:09:12,267 --> 01:09:13,100
Thank you.

1698
01:09:13,100 --> 01:09:14,100
Thank you.

1699
01:09:14,100 --> 01:09:15,033
